📢 RankOne Sport Alert📢

RankOne is up and running! Please go to www.rankonesport.com to electronically fill out your student-athletes forms!

Please read all instructions before filling out your forms.

What are Online Forms - Per OSSAA and Catoosa Public Schools, we require a set of forms to be completed prior to participating in athletic activities. All CPS Athletes 6-12 grades are required to complete these online forms before participation.

The only printed form we need is the physical. They can be turned into the coach or athletic office.

The student ID number is also your students lunch number.

Thanks! 🟩⬛️

Hey MS and HS students—what’s for lunch?

MS and HS eating at school will be able to preorder lunch. Preorders due by 8:30 am each day (you can also order for an entire week at a time).
https://lunchroomzoom.com/catoosa/
Starting Monday, August 24, if MS/HS students want a choice (hot meal listed on menu, hamburger, pizza, chicken sandwich or salad they must preorder). If no preorder, they will go through the line for the hot meal listed on the menu. No preorders for Cherokee or Helen Paul at this time.

See menu here: https://www.catoosaps.net/253599_2

Virtual/Blended Students:
We are working on meals for virtual students and will post info tomorrow. Virtual meal service will start Monday. It will be a pick up service at the Dome each Monday for the entire week.

We hope everyone has a great day tomorrow! It's a great day to be an Indian!

CORRECTION: He will be at Catoosa today (Tuesday) 1:00-3:00

Cherokee Councilman Joe Deere will be at Catoosa Public Schools' Admin Building TUESDAY from 1:00-3:00 to assist Cherokee students and families with the $400 technology initiative and clothing vouchers. Must have Cherokee Nation Citizen Card. Deadline is August 14

Contact Cherokee Nation for more info. https://cherokee.org/all-services/education-services/respond-recover-and-rebuild-education-initiative/

A $150 to students across Cherokee Nation without regard to income or type of schooling they receive for clothes and a winter coat. For income, eligible students it’s a $300 clothing stipend.

A $400 education technology stipend is also offered for any Cherokee student ages 5 to 18 regardless of income and regardless of where they live.

post_text:
Catoosa High School Varsity Cheer

With all of the uncertainty happening around us, so many things have been left up in the air, but we have good news! We are ready to build our new Varsity Cheer Team! Below you’ll find the information you or your student will need if he/she is planning on trying out!

•The clinic for tryouts will be held July 28th and July 29th. It will begin promptly at 4:00, and it will be held in the cheer room located in the Activity Center. Doors will open at 3:30.
•Varsity tryouts will be held on July 30th and will begin at 4:00.
•EVERY student who plans on trying out for cheer MUST stop by the high school office and pick up necessary paperwork. The paperwork will give information on what cheerleaders and parents can expect, permission slips, etc. Paperwork can be picked up beginning on July 15th. The high school office is open M-Th from 8:00-4:00.
•If there are any questions, please contact me, Erin Davis, at varsitycheer@catoosa.k12.ok.us

I look forward to hearing from you and seeing our kids at the clinic!

post_text:
🎓💚Graduation 2020💚🎓
Thursday, May 21, 2020 at McNabb Field at 8:00 p.m.

Seniors will be limited to 10 tickets each to ensure extreme social distancing in the stands.

We appreciate your patience as this decision was being made. We wanted to give our seniors the best experience possible and have been doing a great deal of research to make sure we can safely accommodate our graduation ceremony. Based on input from the city, county and state, we can meet the guidelines for social distancing and safety but there are protocols that will be enforced. Please see the flyer for more information.

All protocols will be strictly enforced. Anyone not following protocols will be escorted out of the stadium. Thank you in advance for your cooperation!

Graduation is subject to change based on local, state, national and/or CDC guidelines.

Alternate dates in case of rain: Friday, May 22 and Saturday, May 23. We will not move the ceremony indoors due to health concerns.

The safety of our students, faculty, and families is our highest priority.

post_text:
Catoosa High School Student High School, in an effort to bridge some of the disconnects we have had over the last several weeks, has developed a Digital Spirit Week! Our hopes are to have ALL members of our community including parents and the little kids participate in the community event! Each day we will upload a video of what that day's spirit day is. You can take a photo or video of the day. Post it to social media with the #K2Community . You can also email your video or photo to K2community@catoosa.k12.ok.us and we will make a video of the submissions!

We hope that you are all being safe and look forward to seeing what this community of Catoosa is all about!

It's A Great Day To Be An Indian!!!

post_text:
This evening, Friday, April 10, Catoosa Public Schools will be joining with schools across the nation in ￼honoring the graduating class of 2020 this evening. We will be turning on the football stadium lights at 20:20 (8:20pm) for 20 minutes and 20 seconds to honor the senior class. Our message to the Seniors, “We are going to burn our stadium lights for you... as a symbol of hope and an assurance that you are on our hearts and minds”!

Please know that this is not a social gathering, but instead a symbol of hope and assurance to the Class of 2020 during these turbulent times!

#BeTheLight
#CatoosaIndians
#Classof2020

The DOME STORM SHELTER will NOT be opened in the event of severe weather until further notice.

We do not have a Dome Manager at this time and since we are in the middle of gathering restrictions we will WAIT to put a manager in place until the restrictions are lifted.

We have not had any applicants for the position of Dome Manager since it was posted in December. If you or someone you know might be interested in volunteering or in employment please complete the application using the link attached. This is only an as-needed position for someone who lives close to the Dome. The position is more about safety than compensation.

Again, the DOME STORM SHELTER will NOT be opened in the event of severe weather until further notice.

https://www.catoosaps.net/471712_3

Wells Middle School parents and students:

YEARBOOK UPDATE:

As we all adapt to change, one thing that remains constant is the yearbook tradition of documenting the history of our students and our school year. We are pleased to announce that our Wells Middle School yearbook is completed and Jostens is working to make sure it is printed!

Since copies are limited and your students will not be returning to school this spring, we ask that you please order your yearbook online as soon as possible. Jostens offers a payment plan at checkout for your purchase if you would like to use that option. They can be reached on the phone at: 1-877-767-5217 or online at: http://jostensyearbooks.com?ref=A06731500

DISTRIBUTION OF THE YEARBOOK:
We are working with the district on plans for distributing the yearbook. We will be communicating with you further as soon as plans are finalized. You WILL receive the yearbook you purchased!

State Superintendent of Public Instruction Joy Hofmeister announced today that she will propose a Continuous Learning Plan to the State Board of Education on Wednesday, March 25, to complete the school year for Oklahoma students without reopening school buildings. It will be recommended that all extracurricular activities be cancelled as well.

We will have information specific to Catoosa Public Schools' plan out very soon.
shared_text:
CONTENT.GOVDELIVERY.COM
Hofmeister proposes State Board of Education approve continuous learning for students starting April 6, school buildings to remain closed

Oklahoma State School Boards Association
March 23 at 3:37 PM ·

State Superintendent of Public Instruction Joy Hofmeister announced today that she will propose a Continuous Learning Plan to the State Board of Education this week to complete the school year for Oklahoma students without reopening school buildings during the global pandemic. While the education of schoolchildren will resume with distance learning, there will not be traditional, in-person instruction or extracurricular activities, instead following critical safety guidance from the Centers for Disease Control with regard to social distancing for students, staff and school families.

The Board will hold a special meeting on Wednesday, March 25. Board members will meet virtually

Track and Baseball Fundraiser Info:

Due to the recent circumstances and not going back to school we will be extending our fundraiser through April 6th. When we come back to school we will talk with our athletes about turning in packets at that time. We have talked with Adrenaline Fundraising and they have extended our sale for us. We ask that your athletes continue to sell for our track/baseball program. Reminder we have the ability for students to accept payment via credit/debit card. If you don’t feel comfortable holding onto the packet with money in it, I will be at the football locker room on Monday, March 23rd from 8:00 am to 12:00 pm and Tuesday, March 24th from 4:00 pm-7:00 pm. You bring the packets to me then. Thanks so much for your support and concern, be safe. Creating Champions For Life!

Sincerely,

Coach Heath
Head boys Track

Information from Catoosa Public Schools regarding the mandatory extension of Spring Break due to the Coronavirus Outbreak. Also, we are creating a page on the school website for parents to find updates from the district. It will be posted later.

If you post questions here we will try to answer. You can also email Mrs. O’Donnell at aodonnell@catoosa.k12.ok.us

post_text:
The OSDE has a meeting at 4:00 today to discuss/approve school closure across the state until April 6. State Supt Joy Hofmeister also has a meeting planned with all superintendents across the state tomorrow afternoon (Tuesday) that will provide further guidance.

Catoosa Public Schools administration has been working on a plan for our students and for nutritional needs for the past week. Once we get full guidance (today and tomorrow), we will provide more details on our plans.

It is more important than ever that we stay positive, pull together and do what's best for our kids.
shared_text:
YOUTUBE.COM
Oklahoma State Board of Education - Special Meeting 03/16/2020

Oklahoma State Department of Education
March 16 at 1:30 PM ·

UPDATE: We're experiencing site issues. You can view the meeting directly on YouTube here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7lk--sBXZlQ&feature=emb_title

The Board will discuss and possibly authorize the closure of all Oklahoma public schools beginning March 17 and lasting until April 6 due to the coronavirus/COVID-19.

post_text: Catoosa High School students from Mrs. Yoder and Mrs. Bell's classes had the pleasure of visiting the City of Broken Arrow this afternoon. Students learned about municipalities and city operations. They were able to hear about all the jobs available with in a big city operation. It was a great day to be outside and learn about many career opportunities. #rosedistrict #cityofba #municipaloperations #careers #futureworkforce #itsagreatdaytobeanindian

post_text: We are SO excited to tour the recently opened and new to Tulsa, San Francisco based Holberton School of Tulsa! Here students learn to code and program apps and websites, AR & VR, and/or become a Tech Entrepreneur. Students from Catoosa High School are fortunate to be able to tour the school and learn about the Tech opportunities in their own backyard . Thank you Holberton School for having us. #holbertonschooloftulsa #coding #programming #thenextstep #techcareers #tulsa #oklahoma

What a GRAND week we have had at Helen Paul Learning Center! We have shared lots of giggles, hugs and reading opportunities with loved ones. QuikTrip generously donated 600 cookies for our guests. Teachers were ecstatic to receive over 150 books to add to their classroom libraries. Please feel free to stop by and shop the Bookfair next Monday and Tuesday. We will have extended hours during conference nights 8:00am-7:00pm.

Happy Reading!
Mrs. Zilmer (Media Specialist)

VISION AND GOALS SURVEY: WE NEED YOUR INPUT

Thank you so much for your participation in the first survey to provide input for our shared core values and purpose!! A representative team with members from all of our school sites has met several times to analyze the survey results received and is working on the draft version of the core values and purpose.

Now we need your input on the VISION and GOALS for Catoosa Public Schools.
